Overload.descr:
Description Returns the absolute value of number.
Returns Absolute value of number.

Description Checks if given IP address is within given range (including both bounding addresses). All IP addresses should be specified as strings.
Returns TRUE if address is within given range, FALSE otherwise.

Description Checks if given IP address is within given subnet (including subnet and broadcast addresses).
Returns TRUE if address is within given subnet, FALSE otherwise.

Description Read parameter's value directly from agent on given node.
Returns Value of given parameter on success and NULL on failure.

Description
Returns

Description Bind all NetXMS objects that can be bound from console (nodes, subnets, clusters, and another containers) to container objects.
Returns Nothing.

Description Round up value.
Returns The smallest integral value that is not less than x.

Description Return a character from it's UNICODE value.
Returns A character.

Description Returns the class name for given object.
Returns Object's class name. If parameter passed to this function is not an object, runtime error will be generated.

Description Create container object.
Returns Reference to newly created object.

Description Create new DCI.
Returns DCI object on success or NULL on failure.

Param.name: node, source, name, description, dataType, pollingInterval, retentionTime

Overload.descr:
Description Create new SNMP transport object for specific node. The node must support SNMP.
Returns Object of class SNMP_Transport or NULL on failure.

Description Delete node's custom attribute.
Returns Nothing.

Description Delete object.
Returns Nothing.

Description Returns the hexidecimal value of a decimal.
Returns Hexadecimal value of number.

Description Exit from script.
Returns Nothing.

Description Returns e (the base of natural logarithms) raised to a power.
Returns e^power expressed as a real number.

Description Find DCI by description (search is case-insensetive).
Returns DCI ID on success or 0 if DCI with matching description was not found.

Description Find DCI by name (search is case-insensetive).
Returns DCI ID on success or 0 if DCI with matching name was not found.

Description Find node object by node id or node name.
Returns Node object with given id or name on success or NULL on failure (either because node with given name/id does not exist, or access to it was denied).

Description Find NetXMS object by object id or name.
Returns Node object with given id or name on success or NULL on failure (either because object with given name/id does not exist, or access to it was denied).

Description Find situation instance either by situation object name and instance name or by situation object ID and instance name (name search is case-insensetive).
Returns Situation object with given ID or name on success or NULL on failure.

Description Round down value.
Returns The largest integral value not greater than x.

Description Formats a numeric value.
Returns Formatted numeric value.

Description Get the average value of the DCI for the given period. The DCI value must be of numeric type.
Returns Average value or NULL on failure.

Description Get value of server's configuration variable.
Returns Value of requested variable or specified default value if given variable is not set.

Description Get value of node's custom attribute. If attribute name conforms to NXSL identifier naming conventions, it can be accessed directly as node object attribute. For example "GetCustomAttribute($node, "my_attribute")" can be changed to "$node->my_attribute".
Returns String value of requested custom attribute or NULL if attribute is missing.

Description Get DCI object with given ID.
Returns DCI object with given id on success or NULL on failure (if object with given id does not exist, or access to it was denied).

Description Get last raw value (before transformation) of DCI with given ID on given node.
Returns Last raw value (before transformation) for given DCI or NULL if DCI with given ID does not exist or has no collected values.

Description Get last value of DCI with given ID on given node.
Returns Last value for given DCI or NULL if DCI with given ID does not exist or has no collected values.

Description Get last value of DCI with given description on given node.
Returns Last value for given DCI or NULL if DCI with given description does not exist or has no collected values.

Description Get last value of DCI with given name on given node.
Returns Last value for given DCI or NULL if DCI with given name does not exist or has no collected values.

Description Get value of event's named parameter.
Returns String value of requested parameter or NULL if no such parameter exist.

Description Get interface name by index.
Returns Name of the requested interface or null if not found.

Description Get interface object by index.
Returns An interface object, or null if not found.

Description Get the maximum value of the DCI for the given period. The DCI value must be of numeric type.
Returns Maximum value or NULL on failure.

Description Get the minimum value of the DCI for the given period. The DCI value must be of numeric type.
Returns Minimum value or NULL on failure.

Description Get all interfaces for given node.
Returns Array of objects of class Interface, with first object placed at index 0. End of list indicated by array element with NULL value.

Description Get accessible parent objects for given node.
Returns Array of objects of class NetObj (generic NetXMS object), with first object placed at index 0. End of list indicated by array element with NULL value. This function will never return template or policy objects applied to node. Return value also affected by trusted nodes settings (see "Security Issues" on wiki for more information).

Description Get accessible child objects for given object.
Returns Array of objects of class Node, Interface, or NetObj, with first object placed at index 0. End of list indicated by array element with NULL value. Return value also affected by trusted nodes settings (see "Security Issues" on wiki for more information).

Description Get accessible parent objects for given object.
Returns Array of objects of class NetObj (generic NetXMS object), with first object placed at index 0. End of list indicated by array element with NULL value. This function will never return template or policy objects applied to node. Return value also affected by trusted nodes settings (see "Security Issues" on wiki for more information).

Description Get the sum value of the DCI for the given period. The DCI value must be of numeric type.
Returns Sum value or NULL on failure.

Description
Returns

Description Converts time in UNIX format (number of seconds since epoch) to calendar date and time broken down into its components, expressed as UTC (or GMT timezone). Function uses either time given in time argument or current time if time is omitted.
Returns Object of class TIME.

Description Returns the position of the first occurrence of substring in string at or after position if specifed. All index values are 1-based (i.e. the first character has index 1, not 0).
Returns Integer value of the position substring was found at, will return 0 if not found.

Description Check if given value is an element of given list.
Returns TRUE if given value is an element of given list, FALSE otherwise.

Description Returns the string of length characters of string, optionally padded with pad character instead of a space.
Returns String of the left length characters.

Description Returns the length of string.
Returns Integer length of the string passed to the function.

Description Converts time in UNIX format (number of seconds since epoch) to calendar date and time broken down into its components. Function uses either time given in time argument or current time if time is omitted.
Returns Object of class TIME.

Description Calculates natural logarithm of given value.
Returns Natural logarithm of x.

Description Calculates logarithm of given value to base 10.
Returns Logarithm of x to base 10.

Description Converts string to lowercase.
Returns Source string converted to lowercase.

Description Removes blanks (space and tab characters) from the left side of specified string.
Returns Source string with blanks at the left side removed.

Description Set object into managed state. Has no effect if object is already in managed state.
Returns Nothing.

Description Returns the value which corresponds to a specified key from specified Mapping Table.
Returns Value corresponding for a keyName from tableName.

Description Returns maximal value from a list of values.
Returns Maximal value of numbers.

Description Returns minimal value from a list of values.
Returns Minimal value of numbers.

Description Convert a character into it's ASCII/Unicode value. Only processes one character.
Returns An ASCII/Unicode value.

Description Post event on behalf of given node. "..." - 0 or more event-specific parameters.
Returns TRUE if event was posted successfully or FALSE if not.

Description Calculates x raised to the power of y.
Returns x raised to the power of y.

Description Generate pseudo random number in given range. Uses c/c++ rand() function.
Returns Random value in range minValue..maxValue.

Description Rename object.
Returns Nothing.

Description Returns the string of length characters of string, optionally padded with pad character instead of blank (space) starting from the right. Padding occurs on the left portion of the string.
Returns String of the right length characters.

Description Returns the position of the last occurrence of substring in string up to or before position if specifed.
Returns Integer value of the position substring was found at, will return 0 if not found.

Description Round floating point value to the nearest integral value or floating point value with given precision. [precision] - optional number of decimal places to be left. If omited or set to 0, x will be rounded to integral value.
Returns The integral value that is closest to x if precision is omited or set to 0, or floating point value rounded to have given number of decimal places.

Description Removes blanks (space and tab characters) from the right side of specified string.
Returns Source string with blanks at the right side removed.

Description Suspend script execution for given number of milliseconds.
Returns Nothing.

Description Format system uptime in seconds as string in format "n days, hh:mm".
Returns System uptime in format "n days, hh:mm".

Description Set value of node's custom attribute. If attribute was not defined, it will be created.
Returns Previous value of requested custom attribute or NULL if attribute was not defined before.

Description Set value of event's named parameter.
Returns Nothing.

Description Set expected state for given interface.
Returns Nothing.

Description Get the object value from specific node with SNMP GET request. The node and all SNMP communication details defined by SNMP transport.
Returns Object of class SNMP_VarBind or NULL on failure.

Description Get the object value from specific node with SNMP GET request. The node and all SNMP communication details defined by SNMP transport. This function is similar to SNMPGet but returns string instead of an SNMP_VarBind object.
Returns String with the value requested or NULL on failure.

Description Assign a specific value to the given SNMP object for the node. The node and all SNMP communication details defined by SNMP transport.
Returns TRUE on success, FALSE in case of failure.

Description Get an array of the object values from specific node with SNMP WALK request. The node and all SNMP communication details defined by SNMP transport.
Returns Array of SNMP_VarBind objects or NULL on failure.

Description
Returns

Description Extracts the substring from string that begins at the nth character and is of length len.
Returns Extracted substring.

Description Gets the system time.
Returns System time as number of seconds elapsed since midnight (00:00:00), January 1, 1970, coordinated universal time, according to the system clock (also known as UNIX time).

Description Writes message to netxms main log at given debug level.
Returns Nothing.

Description Removes blanks (space and tab characters) from both sides of specified string.
Returns Source string with blanks at both sides removed.

Description Returns the data type for given value.
Returns data type for given value. Type is returned as lowercase string. The following type names can be returned: NULL object string real int32 int64 uint32 uint64

Description Remove (unbind) object from a container.
Returns Nothing.

Description Set object into unmanaged state. Has no effect if object is already in unmanaged state.
Returns Nothing.

Description Converts string to uppercase.
Returns Source string converted to uppercase.
